[3] El Salvador
Date: 6 Oct 2003
From: ProMED <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: EFE 3 Oct 2003 [edited]
<http://www.efenews.com/>

Salvadorean Health Minister Herbert Betancourt issued a
nationwide alert on Friday in response to a new outbreak of classic
and hemorrhagic dengue.
Since January [2003], 1365 cases of the classic variety of the
disease have been reported in El Salvador and 75 of the potentially
deadly DHF, which has already taken the lives of 4 people,
Betancourt said. In 2002, El Salvador experienced a dengue fever
epidemic that killed 10 people after infecting a [reported] total of
4780.
