[4] Honduras
Date: 6 Oct 2003
From: ProMED <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: EFE 3 Oct 2003 [edited]
<http://www.efenews.com/>

Hemorrhagic dengue has infected 68 people in northern Honduras,
including 10 in the past few days, a health official said Friday.
Danilo Cruz, director of Mario Catarino Rivas Hospital, where most
of the patients -- children between the ages of 3 and 11 -- have
been admitted, told reporters that "the epidemic is spreading."
Cruz said that so far 5 people have died of hemorrhagic dengue
fever. The latest, on Thursday, was the wife of the former head of
the Permanent Commission for Contingencies (COPECO). Cruz
said all the patients are from communities near San Pedro Sula.
Health authorities say more than 2300 cases of classic dengue
fever have been reported so far in 2003, a 70 percent drop from
2002.
